blog.name: sharoncartercomics
blog.title: Agent 13
blog.description:
In this blog, I’ll be posting comic book panels featuring Marvel's Sharon Carter / Agent 13 - Captain America's favourite spy! 

There is probably not going to be any movie stuff here, because that seems to be most of the Sharon Carter fan content out there.

She’s got a great, deep history in the comics, and I’d like to chronicle that.

And in so doing, hopefully put out some positive Sharon Carter content into the world.

Twitter: @agent13comics

summary: Small piece of madness before bed - The Doctor in the MCU
body:
Small piece of madness before bed - The Doctor in the MCU

Just a little something.

Captain Marvel arrives on earth following the events of infinity war. Its a mess, a god awful mess.

“I know someone who can help” she says, she turns to Tony, “Can I borrow your phone?”

Not long after, a familiar wheezing noise fills the Avengers tower, a blue box appears from nowhere.

The door opens, but nobody leaves.

“This isn’t right”, thinks the captain, “You guys stay here” she say.

Tentatively, she enters the TARDIS.

The Doctor is standing at the console, everything appears normal. “Doctor?” she asks.

“Carol! Brilliant! It’s been ages!”

“Doctor, thank god you’ve come, something terrible has happened!”

“I’ve been monitoring the effect from here” said the Doctor “This is not just earth, half of all life in the universe has been erased.”

“We got to come up with a plan Doctor, we need a strategy, a way to do undo this. I’ll introduce to the Avengers”

“The Avengers? Really? That’s a great name! Proper impressive”

“Come outside, Tony is going to love meeting you.”

Carol made for the door, but stopped, the Doctor wasn’t following.

“Doctor? Is somethings wrong, what’s happened?”

“I can’t go outside Carol.”

“You can’t go outside? You’re not nervous surely, all the people you’ve met, Tony Stark isn’t that intimidating.”

“It’s not that Carol. I physically can’t leave the TARDIS.”

“You can’t leave? Why can’t you” Carol stopped, “He erased you didn’t he?”

“Kind of.” Said the Doctor. “My existence in that dimension has been erased, Thanos must have targeted people he though were a threat.”

The Doctor looked to the doorway, a sad look in her face.

“While I’m in this dimension, inside the TARDIS, it doesn’t effect me, as soon as I leave this dimension…”
